<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE exercise
  SYSTEM "../Symbols.dtd">
<exercise xmlns="Compositor" id="Exe_BoxesAsProductsIntervals">
	  <caption>Expressing Boxes as a Product of Intervals</caption>
	  <problem>
      <problem.body>
		       <para>
            <para.body>Express each of the following objects as a product of intervals.</para.body>
         </para>
	     </problem.body>
   </problem>
	  <part.exercise>
		    <problem>
         <problem.body>
			         <para>
               <para.body>The rectangle in <math>
                     <latex>\RNr[2]</latex>
                  </math> with corner points <math>
                     <latex>(-2,-2), (2,-2), (-2,2), (2,2)</latex>
                  </math>.</para.body>
            </para>
		       </problem.body>
      </problem>
		    <approach version="1">
			      <answer.exercise>
            <answer.exercise.block>
               <answer.exercise.block.body>
				              <para>
                     <para.body>The given rectangle consists of all points in the product <math>
                           <latex>[-2,2]\times [-2,2]</latex>
                        </math>.</para.body>
                  </para>
			            </answer.exercise.block.body>
            </answer.exercise.block>
         </answer.exercise>
			      <solution.hint>
				        <para>
               <para.body>Answer first the following aspects of this problem:</para.body>
            </para>
				        <ol>
					          <li>
						            <para>
                     <para.body>What is the interval of numbers <math>
                           <latex>x</latex>
                        </math> which appear as the first coordinate of a point inside the given box?</para.body>
                  </para>
					          </li>
					          <li>
						            <para>
                     <para.body>What is the interval of numbers <math>
                           <latex>y</latex>
                        </math>  which appear as the second coordinate of a point inside the given box?</para.body>
                  </para>
					          </li>
				        </ol>
				        <para>
               <para.body>If you have answers to these two questions and still do not now how to proceed, you need to review the material on how to concatenate tuples of numbers to form a product of spaces of tuples.</para.body>
            </para>
			      </solution.hint>
		    </approach>
	  </part.exercise>
	
	  <part.exercise>
		    <problem>
         <problem.body>
			         <para>
               <para.body>The box in <math>
                     <latex>\RNr[3]</latex>
                  </math> with corner points</para.body>
            </para>
			         <math.display>
				           <latex>(0,0,0), (3,0,0), (0,5,0), (3,5,0), (0,0,7), (3,0,7), (0,5,7), (3,5,7)</latex>
			         </math.display>
		       </problem.body>
      </problem>
		    <approach version="1">
			      <answer.exercise>
            <answer.exercise.block>
               <answer.exercise.block.body>
				              <para>
                     <para.body>The given box consists of all points in the product <math>
                           <latex>[0,3]\times [0,5]\times [0,7]</latex>
                        </math>.</para.body>
                  </para>
			            </answer.exercise.block.body>
            </answer.exercise.block>
         </answer.exercise>
			      <solution.hint>
				        <para>
               <para.body>Answer first the following aspects of this problem:</para.body>
            </para>
				        <ol>
					          <li>
						            <para>
                     <para.body>What is the interval of numbers <math>
                           <latex>x</latex>
                        </math> which appear as the first coordinate of a point inside the given box?</para.body>
                  </para>
					          </li>
					          <li>
						            <para>
                     <para.body>What is the interval of numbers <math>
                           <latex>y</latex>
                        </math>  which appear as the second coordinate of a point inside the given box?</para.body>
                  </para>
					          </li>
					          <li>
						            <para>
                     <para.body>What is the interval of numbers <math>
                           <latex>z</latex>
                        </math>  which appear as the third coordinate of a point inside the given box?</para.body>
                  </para>
					          </li>
				        </ol>
				        <para>
               <para.body>If you have answers to these two questions and still do not now how to proceed, you need to review the material on how to concatenate tuples of numbers to form a tuple in a product of spaces.</para.body>
            </para>
			      </solution.hint>
			      <solution>
            <solution.body>
				           <para>
                  <para.body>Let <math>
                        <latex>(x,y,z)</latex>
                     </math> denote a point in the box with the specified corners.</para.body>
               </para>
				           <ol>
					             <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>The first coordinates of the corner points are <math>
                              <latex>0</latex>
                           </math> and <math>
                              <latex>3</latex>
                           </math>. Therefore <math>
                              <latex>0\leq x\leq 3</latex>
                           </math>.</para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
					             <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>The second coordinates of the corner points are <math>
                              <latex>0</latex>
                           </math> and <math>
                              <latex>5</latex>
                           </math>. Therefore <math>
                              <latex>0\leq y\leq 5</latex>
                           </math>.</para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
					             <li>
                     <para>
                        <para.body>The third coordinates of the corner points are <math>
                              <latex>0</latex>
                           </math> and <math>
                              <latex>7</latex>
                           </math>. Therefore <math>
                              <latex>0\leq z\leq 7</latex>
                           </math>.</para.body>
                     </para>
                  </li>
				           </ol>
				           <para>
                  <para.body>Therefore the given box consists of all points in the product of intervals</para.body>
               </para>
				           <math.display>
					             <latex>[0,3]\times [0,5]\times [0,7]</latex>
				           </math.display>
			         </solution.body>
         </solution>
		    </approach>
	  </part.exercise>
</exercise>
